					<section id="side_tab2" class="item" data-title="The Global Goals">
						<div class="item-content">

				            <h1 class="white">The Global Goals</h1>
				            <p><strong>Background</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>On 25<sup>th</sup> September 2015, countries adopted a set of <strong>goals to end poverty, protect the planet</strong>, and <strong>ensure prosperity for all</strong> as part of the new <a target="_target" href="http://www.un.org/ga/search/view_doc.asp?symbol=A/RES/70/1&Lang=E">Sustainable Development Goals.</a></li>
								<li>For the Goals to be reached, everyone needs to do their part: Governments, the private sector and civil society.</li>
								<li>20 UN leaders recently heralded ICTs as critical in the role of technology for good and delivering against the Goals, highlighted in the UN <a target="_blank" href="http://www.itu.int/en/sustainable-world/Documents/Fast-forward_progress_report_414709 FINAL.pdf">“Fast forward progress”</a> report (July ‘17).</li>
								<li>The UN has declared technology an accelerator for innovation, and that there is no room for complacency in achieving the Goals – the time is now.</li>
							</ul>
							<p><strong>Rationale</strong></p>
							<ul>
								<li>For the Global Goals to be met, the private sector must act. </li>
								<li>It’s the business opportunity of the 21st century – worth $4 trillion today, and at least $12 trillion by 2030. And it exists everywhere, in every sector.</li>
								<li>2030Vision will catalyse technology innovation for the goals right across the private sector.</li>
								<li>The Internet of Things, AI and next generation computing can build a better world for everyone, and the Goals give businesses a universal agenda to make that happen. </li>
							</ul>
				            <div class="cta-row">
				              <a href="http://www.globalgoals.org" target="_blank" class="btn dark-blue">More on The Global Goals</a>
				            </div>
				        </div>
				      </section>

